structors in Native Images; it may not allow arbitrary reflection. I wonder if native image tests might exclude JDK classes and if I should use a cglib class with a public constructor for a primitive array.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring constructor and method descs**\\n\\nI'm thinking about how to find a constructor or method descriptor that supports package fallbacks and primitive arrays without relying on JDK reflection metadata. The dynamic access records for the class come from a library, but I might still need metadata for the reflected constructor at runtime. It seems like I could choose a cglib class that has a public constructor, perhaps even a String, and use `findConstructor` with the fully qualified cglib path. This could be an effective approach!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering code formatting**\\n\\nI’m feeling a bit uncertain about the code right now. It seems safer to ensure all top-level public elements are correctly set. I wonder if I should also remove any extra blank lines before closing. It might satisfy the checkstyle, even though it feels not entirely important. But still, I think it's a good habit to maintain clean formatting. Let's see how it looks once those adjustments are made!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tsuWs97ggabnvQVVlPjplJxD|fc_0e6ab983e6cb0a45016a26b914c2288194bec6799dd8b6eee1", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/cglib/cglib-nodep/2.2.2/src/test/java/cglib/cglib_nodep/ReflectUtilsTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "        constructor.visitEnd();\n    }\n\n}\n", "newText": "        constructor.visitEnd();\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1255, "output": 845, "cacheRead": 57344, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59444, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1780922622115, "responseId": "resp_0e6ab983e6cb0a45016a26